article.headline: McCoughtry scores 31 as No. 13 Louisville slams Kentucky
article.linkText: McCoughtry, No. 13 Louisville blow by Kentucky
article.story:
LOUISVILLE, Ky. -- Angel McCoughtry scored 31 points to lead Louisville (No. 13 ESPN/USA Today, No. 12 AP) to a 75-59 victory over Kentucky on Sunday.

Candyce Bingham had 14 points and 12 rebounds and Deseree' Byrd added 10 points and nine assists for the Cardinals (9-1), who forced 26 turnovers. Monique Reid scored 12 points.

Lydia Watkins led Kentucky (5-5) with 15 points, going 6-for-6 from the field. Eleia Roddy had 13 points and 15 rebounds.

The crowd of 16,337 set the Louisville, state of Kentucky and Big East Conference paid attendance record for a women's basketball game.

Louisville shot 32 percent from the field in the first half but still led 33-21 at the break.

McCoughtry also had six of the Cardinals' 14 steals, and Monique Reid finished with 12 points.

Carly Morrow had 14 points for the Wildcats, who outrebounded Louisville 39-34.
